@startuml MatchMonitorClassification_MainFlow
title Match Monitor Classification (General) - Main Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #1976D2
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D

|Job 1: Update Status Match Monitor|
start
:Trigger: Periodic (Every 30 mins);
note right
  **Purpose**: Maintain match status
  **Endpoint**: /api/classificationJobs/
                UpdateStatusMatchMonitor
end note

:Start Service;

|DataAccess|
:GetMatchMonitor();
note right
  **SP**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_
         MatchMonitor_Get
  **Returns**: List<int> MatchIDs
  **Logic**: Get unfinished matches
end note

:Return MatchIDs[];

|Service|
if (Has MatchIDs?) then (yes)
  :Convert to comma-separated string;
  note right
    Example: "12345,67890,11111"
  end note
  
  |DataAccess|
  :GetMatchInfosByIDs(matchIDs);
  note right
    **SP**: CTS_MatchInfo_Get
    **Database**: MainDB (SQL Server)
    **Returns**: MatchesInfosEntity[]
    - MatchID
    - EventStatus (Pre-match/Live/Closed)
    - HomeName, AwayName
  end note
  
  :Return Match Infos[];
  
  |Service|
  if (Has Match Infos?) then (yes)
    :Extract MatchStatusModel[];
    note right
      **Model**:
      - MatchID
      - EventStatus
    end note
    
    |DataAccess|
    :UpdateStatusMatchMonitor(matchStatuses);
    note right
      **SP**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_
             MatchMonitor_UpdateMatch
      **Input**: JSON of match statuses
      **Update**: EventStatus for each match
    end note
  endif
endif

|Job 1|
:Complete;
stop

|Job 2: Classify Match Monitor|
start
:Trigger: Every 5 minutes;
note right
  **Purpose**: Detect fraud & classify customers
  **Endpoint**: /api/classificationJobs/
                ClassifyMatchMonitor
  **Batch Size**: 500 (fixed)
end note

:Start Service;

|DataAccess|
:ClassifyMatchMonitor();
note right
  **SP**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_
         MatchMonitor_Classify
  **Returns**: 3 result sets
  1. ClassifyGBMMCustInfosEntity[]
  2. MMDetailIDList (string)
  3. MatchID (int?)
  
  **Logic**: 
  - Select ONE match (FIFO)
  - Run detection rules
  - Return fraud tickets
end note

:Return ClassifyGBMatchMonitorModel;
note right
  **Model Contains**:
  - CustInfos[] (customers to classify)
  - MMDetailIDList (fraud ticket IDs)
  - MatchID (current match)
end note

|Service|
if (Has CustInfos?) then (yes)
  :Convert to InsertProblemAccountEntity[];
  note right
    **Entity Fields**:
    - CustID
    - SportGroupID
    - CategoryID (CC type)
    - Reason
    - FunctionId: ClassifyGBMatchMonitor
  end note
  
  partition "Insert Problem Account" {
    |ProblemAccountServices|
    :InsertProblemAccountPackage();
    note right
      **Process**:
      1. Validate customers
      2. Insert to CTSCustomerClassification
      3. Update CC category
      4. Mark as PA
      
      **FunctionId**: ClassifyGBMatchMonitor
      **CCInputFlow**: InsertPACategory
      **Returns**: Inserted CustIDs
    end note
    
    :Return CustIDs[];
  }
  
  partition "Push to External" {
    |CustClassToMainDBService|
    :PushExternalProblemAcountPackage(CustIDs);
    note right
      **Push Config**:
      - RoleGroup: Member
      - ExternalBatchSize: 500
      - IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
      - ServiceName: "Match Monitor Classication"
      
      **Process**:
      1. Batch CustIDs (500 per batch)
      2. Push to MainDB
      3. Sync customer classification
    end note
  }
endif

|Service|
:ClassifyMatchMonitorCompleted(model);
note right
  **Mark as Completed**:
  - MatchID (from model)
  - MMDetailIDList (fraud tickets)
end note

|DataAccess|
if (Has MatchID?) then (yes)
  :ClassifyMatchMonitorCompleted(matchID, mmDetailIDs);
  note right
    **SP**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_
           MatchMonitor_Completed
    **Input**:
    - ip_MatchID
    - ip_MMDetailsIDList (comma-separated)
    
    **Update**: IsProcessed = 1 for processed tickets
  end note
endif

|Job 2|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job completes after processing ONE match**:
  - Next run will pick next match in queue
  - FIFO order maintained
  - Failed matches stay in queue for retry
end note

stop

note right
  **Key Characteristics**:
  
  **Job 1 (Update Status)**:
  - Maintenance job
  - Updates all unfinished matches
  - Runs less frequently (30 mins)
  - No classification logic
  
  **Job 2 (Classify)** ⭐:
  - Main detection job
  - Processes ONE match per run
  - Runs frequently (5 mins)
  - Full classification & external push
  
  **Differences from BySport**:
  - General: One match at a time
  - BySport: Multiple matches per run
  - General: Has status update job
  - BySport: No status update
  
  **Processing**:
  - FIFO Queue (First In, First Out)
  - Automatic retry for failures
  - Push to MainDB included
  - Batch size fixed at 500
end note

@enduml

